> Have you heard of Milly? She used to be our supply chain intern and she was an AMAZING cook. She'd always wanted to do a really authentic French recipe. Every now and then she'd give Mimi lots of ideas on French cooking and recipes. That's how Milly's herby chicken was born - and we're not being biased when we say that it's délicieux! She's going to be so happy to have a recipe in your box - she might cry with joy when it goes out. Enjoy this one from our dear Milly!

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 180 degrees. Peel and chop the @red onion{1} into 1 1/2cm chunks and peel and chop the @garlic clove{1}. Cut the @courgette{1} in half lengthways then slice into half moons about 1cm thick. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop it into roughly 2cm chunks. Chop each of the @vine tomatoes{2} into roughly eight pieces.

Pop the veggies and half the garlic on a #baking tray{}, drizzle over @oil{2%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{}. Give the tray a good shake to make sure everything has a coating of oil and herbs.

Put the rest of the chopped garlic in a #bowl{} with the @provençal herbs{1/2%tsp} and @oil{1%tbsp}. Cut three slashes in the skin of the @British chicken breasts{2} and add them to the garlicky herby bowl. Move them around so that the chicken gets a good coating of the mixture, then place the chicken on top of the veggies on the #baking tray{}.

Sprinkle a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @pepper{pinch} over the chicken and put the tray in the oven to cook for ~{30%minutes}. In the last 10 mins of cooking, add @water{50%ml} to the baking tray and pop back in the oven.

Put @water{300%ml} in a #pot{} on medium heat with the @chicken stock pot{1/2}. Once it comes to the boil add in the @couscous{3/4%cup}. Cover the pot with a tightly fitting #lid{}, take this off the heat and leave to the side until the rest of the meal is ready.

When the couscous is ready, fluff it up with a #fork{}. When the chicken is cooked, put it on a #chopping board{} and cut into roughly 2cm slices. Serve the couscous in #bowls{} with the veggies and the slices of chicken arranged on top. Enjoy!